      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "# Simple Citations 1.5.0\n\n## New Features\n\n### Multi bibliography support\n- Multiple Better CSL JSON files can now be registered in settings.\n- Files are prioritized by order; earlier entries take precedence when the same citation key appears in multiple files.\n- Per-property merge strategies: choose **Priority** (use highest-priority file) or **Merge** (combine values from all files) for each field. `collections` and `library` default to Merge.\n- A new **Bibliography** property (opt-in) records which file(s) each citation was sourced from.\n\n### Mobile support\n- Settings UI is now responsive and usable on mobile devices.\n\n### New commands\n- **Sync citations** — adds new notes and updates existing ones in a single step.\n- **Reset all properties (Full sync)** — clears and rewrites all frontmatter properties; shows a confirmation modal before running.\n\n## Contributors\n\n- [@haiqiang-zhang](https://github.com/haiqiang-zhang) — [#7](https://github.com/masaki39/simple-citations/pull/7)\n",
